From: WilhelmOS <anwar.ludin@algonents.com>
Subject: [PATCH] xdg-shell: ignore fullscreen requests before initial commit

wlroots 0.19 asserts (wlr_xdg_surface_schedule_configure:
`surface->initialized`) if a configure is scheduled before the client's
initial commit. Clients such as GLFW request fullscreen at window
creation time, before committing, which crashed cage.

Backport of the guard present in cage master (which targets wlroots
0.20 and cannot be used wholesale): early-return when the toplevel is
not yet initialized. The kiosk view-mapping path fullscreens the
surface after the initial commit anyway.

Upstream-Status: Backport [https://github.com/cage-kiosk/cage/blob/5491610293a59123710861330be92e4c2ec93840/xdg_shell.c]

--- a/xdg_shell.c
+++ b/xdg_shell.c
@@ -188,6 +188,10 @@ handle_xdg_toplevel_request_fullscreen(struct wl_listener *listener, void *data)
 {
 	struct cg_xdg_shell_view *xdg_shell_view = wl_container_of(listener, xdg_shell_view, request_fullscreen);

+	if (!xdg_shell_view->xdg_toplevel->base->initialized) {
+		return;
+	}
+
 	/**
 	 * Certain clients do not like figuring out their own window geometry if they
 	 * display in fullscreen mode, so we set it here.
